<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bulma@0.9.4/css/bulma.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/font-awesome-4.7.0">
  </head>
  <body>    
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title">Icons</h1>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="columns">
          <div class="column">
            <p>We use <a href="https://fontawesome.com/v4.7.0/icons/">Font Awesome 4.7.0 icons</a>.
              I know that Font Awesome 5.0 is more fashionable, but the extra icons are
              not free, and it actually makes debugging harder.
              In software, not everything that is newer is necessarily better! </p>
          </div>
          <div class="column">
            <p>To include an icon, you include a <i class="fa fa-star"></i> tag; look at
              the source code and you will figure it out!
              <a href="https://fontawesome.com/v4.7.0/examples/">Looking at the examples</a>
              is also very useful.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>    
  </body>
</html>